<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,932,1390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1076,1102]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Ashmead, 1904)" authorityName="Wachi &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Ashmead" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[322,756,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hakonensis">
<emphasis box="[322,554,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Andricus hakonensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ashmead, W. H." box="[569,747,1076,1102]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="65 - 84" refId="ref42279" refString="Ashmead, W. H. (1904) Description of new Hymenoptera from Japan (I). Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 12 (3), 65 - 84." type="journal article" year="1904">Ashmead, 1904</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was mentioned as a host gall of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1973" box="[1121,1246,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kovalevi">
<emphasis box="[1121,1246,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. kovalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time in 
<bibRefCitation author="Penzes, Z. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Bihari, P. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G." box="[182,412,1112,1139]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref49869" refString="Penzes, Z., Tang, C. - T., Bihari, P., Bozso, M., Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. (2012) Oak associated inquilines (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae, Synergini). TISCIA Monograph Series, 11, 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="2012">
Pénzes 
<emphasis box="[268,319,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, who stated that 
<bibRefCitation author="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[607,846,1112,1138]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="32 - 33" refId="ref54609" refString="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2009) Taxonomic status of the oak gall wasp Callirhytis hakonensis Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), a candidate for native host of Torymus beneficus Yasumatsu et Kamijo (Hymenoptera: Torymidae), with a description of its sexual generation. In: Moriya, S. (Ed.), A global serious pest of chestnut trees, Dryocosmus kuriphilus: yesterday, today and tomorrow. Proceedings of the Japan-Italy Joint International Symposium, Tsukuba, 2009, pp. 32 - 33." type="journal article" year="2009">Wachi &amp; Abe (2009)</bibRefCitation>
obtained 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abe" authorityYear="1997" box="[960,1089,1112,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masudai">
<emphasis box="[960,1089,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. masudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occasionally from these galls. However, this host gall association is neither mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[806,1038,1148,1174]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="32 - 33" refId="ref54609" refString="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2009) Taxonomic status of the oak gall wasp Callirhytis hakonensis Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), a candidate for native host of Torymus beneficus Yasumatsu et Kamijo (Hymenoptera: Torymidae), with a description of its sexual generation. In: Moriya, S. (Ed.), A global serious pest of chestnut trees, Dryocosmus kuriphilus: yesterday, today and tomorrow. Proceedings of the Japan-Italy Joint International Symposium, Tsukuba, 2009, pp. 32 - 33." type="journal article" year="2009">Wachi &amp; Abe (2009)</bibRefCitation>
nor 
<bibRefCitation author="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[1087,1321,1148,1174]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="322 - 326" refId="ref54708" refString="Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2010) Taxonomic status of the oak gall wasp Callirhytis hakonensis Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the sexual generation. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 103 (3), 322 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 09128" type="journal article" year="2010">Wachi &amp; Abe (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, and other authors have never recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1973" box="[485,613,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kovalevi">
<emphasis box="[485,613,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. kovalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from galls of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wachi &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Ashmead" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[782,939,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hakonensis">
<emphasis box="[782,939,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. hakonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we consider this association as doubtful and have not included it in Table 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,932,1390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1256,1282]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1973" box="[303,515,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kovalevi">
<emphasis box="[303,515,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ceroptres kovalevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from host galls in the genera 
<emphasis box="[1071,1346,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1840" box="[1071,1175,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Andricus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1881" box="[1188,1346,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Plagiotrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Plagiotrochus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ussuraspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ussuraspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as from other undetermined galls, on oaks (
